[30;1m138 | [0m[35mThere are a few concepts used throughout Cog that might be helpful to understand.[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35m- **Config**: The `cog.yaml` file.[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35m- **Image**: Represents a built Docker image that serves the Cog API, containing a **model**.[0m
[30;1m142 | [0m[35m- **Input**: Input from a **prediction**, as key/value JSON object.[0m
[30;1m143 | [0m[35m- **Model**: A user's machine learning model, consisting of code and weights.[0m
[30;1m144 | [0m[35m- **Output**: Output from a **prediction**, as arbitrarily complex JSON object.[0m
